I'm new to ruby and I want to play around with conversions.  However, I can't get it to work correctly.

$ ruby -v
ruby 1.9.3p327 (2012-11-10 revision 37606) [x86_64-darwin12.2.0]

$ gem install conversions
Fetching: conversions-1.4.6.gem (100%)
Successfully installed conversions-1.4.6
1 gem installed

$ cat test.rb 
require 'conversions'   

puts 5.miles.to.kilometers

$ ruby test.rb 
/Users/i/.rvm/gems/ruby-1.9.3-p327/gems/conversions-1.4.6/lib/conversions/unit.rb:26:in `to': wrong number of arguments (0 for 1) (ArgumentError)
    from test.rb:3:in`<main>'

It seems that lib/conversions/default_table.rb is missing or incomplete.

